---
import SectionHeading from "@/components/SectionHeading.astro";
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "@/site.config";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Haley Parks, an AI Product Engineer building personal AI systems, human modeling tools, and adaptive performance systems."
>
  <section class="page-section container text-page">
    <SectionHeading
      eyebrow="About"
      title="Hi, I'm Haley."
      text="I'm a software engineer, data analyst, and someone who naturally sees the world as interconnected systems."
    />

    <p>
      I enjoy building systems that help people better understand themselves and
      make better decisions. My work usually starts with a messy human problem,
      then turns into software, data models, dashboards, automation, or
      conversational interfaces that can be used, evaluated, and improved.
    </p>

    <h2>How I think and build</h2>
    <p>
      I am drawn to systems where the interesting part is not one isolated
      metric, page, or workflow, but the relationships between them. Context
      matters. History matters. Goals change. Good tools should help people
      notice those patterns instead of asking them to hold everything in their
      heads.
    </p>

    <p>
      The philosophy behind much of my work is simple: give the machines the
      burden of remembering, coordinating, searching, and connecting. Give
      people their attention back.
    </p>

    <h2>Bodybuilding and The Human Model</h2>
    <p>
      Outside of work, I am also a bodybuilder. Like many athletes, I wanted a
      deeper understanding of my training than current wearables and fitness
      apps could provide.
    </p>

    <p>
      Recovery metrics are useful, and I rely heavily on data from my Apple
      Watch, but they only tell part of the story. They do not tell me how well
      I am moving, how much force I am producing, how much effort a set actually
      required, or whether I am creating the training stimulus I intended.
    </p>

    <p>
      The Human Model began as an attempt to answer those questions for myself.
      Along the way, it became something much bigger: an AI-powered research
      platform where I can experiment with wearable data, biomechanics, machine
      learning, conversational interfaces, and decision-support systems to
      better understand how people adapt over time.
    </p>

    <p>
      And if it helps me earn a bodybuilding trophy along the way, I won't
      complain.
    </p>

    <h2>Professional focus</h2>
    <p>
      My current work focuses on AI product engineering, personal AI systems,
      human modeling, adaptive performance systems, human-centered automation,
      and decision-support systems.
    </p>

    <h2>Opportunities</h2>
    <p>
      {siteConfig.availability}
    </p>

    <ul class="quiet-list split-list">
      <li>AI product engineering</li>
      <li>Personal AI systems</li>
      <li>Human modeling</li>
      <li>Adaptive performance systems</li>
      <li>Human-centered automation</li>
      <li>Decision-support systems</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      You can reach me at
      <a href={`mailto:${siteConfig.email}`}>{siteConfig.email}</a>, find my
      code on <a href={siteConfig.githubUrl}>GitHub</a>, or connect with me on
      <a href={siteConfig.linkedinUrl}>LinkedIn</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
